        "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
        "body": "This is definitely a bug. While it can be argued that `nan` should not be treated as a \"null\" value (since we have dedicated null values), the behaviour of `.groupby.fillna(method=\"ffill\")` should be consistent with `.fillna(method=\"ffill\")` (which fills `nan`):\r\n\r\n```python\r\nIn [64]: s\r\nOut[64]:\r\n0    0.0\r\n1    1.0\r\n2    2.0\r\n3    NaN\r\ndtype: float64\r\n\r\nIn [65]: s.fillna(method=\"ffill\")\r\nOut[65]:\r\n0    0.0\r\n1    1.0\r\n2    2.0\r\n3    2.0\r\ndtype: float64\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo we should either never fill nans, or always fill nans.",
